This module provides utilities for integrating with the Firebase Admin SDK.

It handles the initialization of the Firebase Admin app and provides access to the Firestore database.

## Key Exports

*   `getAdminApp()`: Initializes and returns the Firebase Admin `App` instance. It checks if an app is already initialized and returns the existing one if available. It reads Firebase credentials from environment variables (`FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID`, `FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL`, `FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY`).
*   `getAdminDb()`: Initializes and returns the Firestore `Firestore` instance. It uses the `getAdminApp()` function to get the Firebase app instance and caches the Firestore instance for subsequent calls.

## Usage

Ensure that the following environment variables are set:

*   `FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID`: Your Firebase project ID.
*   `FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL`: The client email for your Firebase service account.
*   `FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY`: The private key for your Firebase service account.

```typescript
import { getAdminDb } from './firebase-admin';

async function getUserData(userId: string) {
  const db = getAdminDb();
  const userDoc = await db.collection('users').doc(userId).get();
  if (userDoc.exists) {
    return userDoc.data();
  } else {
    return null;
  }
}
```
